cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with optimizing content caching at base stations. It also involves learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves recommendation systems, which could place it in the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The joint optimization problem formulation and the use of a greedy algorithm suggest that it could also belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
